TITLE: Configure `tsconfig.json` for Node.js built-in type stripping
DESCRIPTION: Node.js's built-in type stripping feature is designed to be lightweight and works optimally with specific `tsconfig.json` settings, especially for TypeScript 5.8 or newer. This configuration ensures compatibility and proper behavior, with the `noEmit` option being optional if you only intend to execute `.ts` files without generating JavaScript output.

SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/node/blob/main/doc/api/typescript.md#_snippet_2

