TITLE: Run Node.js application with Amaro for monorepo TypeScript development
DESCRIPTION: This bash command demonstrates how to run a Node.js application in a monorepo setup, leveraging Amaro for type stripping and the `--conditions=typescript` flag. This configuration allows Node.js to load TypeScript source files directly from linked packages, enabling immediate reflection of changes during development.

SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/node/blob/main/deps/amaro/README.md#_snippet_5

